@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

Introduction to @{b}DocMa@{ub}


@{b}DocMa@{ub} is a @{"MUI" link "ReadMe.mui/main"} based Multimedia Document Manager.
It displays directories in an icon list. Each icon is specified by the filetype of the
directory entry. You can start applications with the icons as argument by doubleclicking on
the icon, open new windows, drag icons between windows, delete or rename files and last but not
least calculate thumbnails from picture files. Therefore @{b}DocMa@{ub} uses the
datatype system. So you can read in every picture file for which you have a
datatype (you can find them e.g. in the aminet drawer "util/dtype").
CyberGraphX, Picasso96  and the new Picture Datatype V43 are supported.
With the "docmafr.library" there is a filerquester with the same
interface as the asl library has. It is possible to patch the asl
library to use the @{b}DocMa@{ub} requester for selectable programs.
Here is a little @{"Preview" link "Preview/main"} for those who can`t imagine what @{b}DocMa@{ub} should
look like.


@{b}DocMa@{ub} is shareware, so if you like it and want to use it in
future: please @{"register" link "DocMaRegister" 0} it!
Then you will get a keyfile which will supress the "nerv-requester" (see
@{"Legal stuff" link "Legal" 0}).

@endnode

