@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

Requirements to run @{b}DocMa@{ub}


@{b}DocMa@{ub} should work on all Amigas with WB 3.x, MUI 3.6 and
better. It`s recommended to have at least a 68030 and a lot of memory, if you want
@{b}DocMa@{ub} to calculate thumbnails of big pictures.
If you want to display true-color thumbnails, you have to install
Picasso96 or CyberGraphX and the new Picture Datatype V43.

@endnode

@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "Installation" "Installation"

Installation of @{b}DocMa@{ub}


Just use the installation skript. After the installation you can find it in the
"DOCMA:Tools" directory, because you also can use it to deinstall
@{b}DocMa@{ub}. If you
will use it from shell, you have to type: "Installer defuser average
Install-DocMa".

@endnode

@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "DocMa" "Start"

Starting @{b}DocMa@{ub}


You can start @{b}DocMa@{ub} from either Workbench or Shell.


@{u}@{b}Starting from Workbench:@{ub}@{uu}

Just doubleclick on the @{b}DocMa@{ub} icon.


@{u}@{b}Starting from Shell:@{ub}@{uu}

Switch to the @{b}DocMa@{ub} drawer and tip in @{b}DocMa@{ub} or
type @{b}DocMa@{ub} with the absolute path (if the @{b}DocMa@{ub} drawer isn`t in your search path).
There is currently only one argument: the name of the directory to load. If you
leave it, the current directory will be loaded.


@{u}@{b}Usage of DocMa@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}DocMa@{ub} opens a window with an icon list of the current directory. There are a lot
of @{"buttons" link "Buttons" 0} in the window and an associated @{"menu" link "Menu" 0}.
The @{"list" link "List" 0} itself has also some functionality.

@endnode

@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "DocMaPref" "DocMaPref"

@{b}DocMa@{ub} configuration editor


Configures @{b}DocMa@{ub}. "Save" saves the configuration and uses it. "Use"
makes the sam, but don`t saves it. "Cancel" changes nothing. The several
configuration possibilities are:


@{"Filetypes" link "Filetypes" 0}

@{"Icons" link "Icons" 0}

@{"DocMaPatch" link "Config_DocMaPatch" 0}

@endnode

@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "DocMaPatch" "DocMaPatch"

Asl library patch program


Patches the asl library to use the @{b}DocMa@{ub} requester for
@{"selectable" link "DocMaPref" 0} programs. To quit @{b}DocMaPatch@{ub}, just start it
again or use "Exchange".

@endnode

@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "DocMaRegister" "DocMaRegister"

DocMa registration program


@{b}DocMa@{ub} is shareware. You have to register it, if you want to
use it in future. That would also be a reason for me to develop new
versions of @{b}DocMa@{ub}. Please use therefore the @{"registration tool" system "DOCMA:DocMaRegister"}.

@endnode

@REM------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "Buttons" "Buttons"

Buttons of the main window(s)


@{b}Volumes:@{ub}

Load a list of available volumes.


@{b}Assigns:@{ub}

Load a list of available assigns.


@{b}Drawer:@{ub}

The current drawer.


@{b}Parent:@{ub}

Change to the parent directory, if there is one.


@{b}Delete:@{ub}

Delete the selected directories/files. Deletes not only the icons,
but also physically the files on the disk, so be careful!


@{b}Rename:@{ub}

Rename the selected directories/files. A string requester will
pop up for each selected icon.


@{b}Makedir:@{ub}

Create a new directory in the current directory and loads it. An info file
will also be created. (ok, this should be made configureable in the next version).


@{b}Update:@{ub}

Update the thumbnails of the icon list. You have to use it, if
the picture files display only the default image and you want to see a preview
of them.


@{b}Abort:@{ub}

Abort the current operation (e.g. Update). Sometimes it needs
some time (e.g. if @{b}DocMa@{ub} waits for datatypes).

@endnode

